It links against the bcg729 library, included as a git submodule under
third_party/bcg729:

    bcg729 - Copyright (C) Belledonne Communications
    Licensed under the GNU General Public License, version 3 or later.
    https://github.com/BelledonneCommunications/bcg729

bcg729 implements the ITU-T G.729 Annex A/B speech codec. The relevant G.729
patents have expired, so distribution and use of a software G.729 codec is no
longer encumbered in most jurisdictions; verify the situation in yours if in
doubt.

